\ New Font for the TI-99
\ Data Source:   Introduction to Assembly Language for the TI Home Computer
\                by Ralph Molesworth, 1983

\ For use with CAMEL99 Forth

\ "This DATA block redefines the standard character set so that lower case letters
\ appear as "true" lower case with descenders. This means the tails of the
\ p,q,g,j and y can be printed on the screen correctly."

\ We have corrected the characters 91..96. They were non ASCII in the book.
\ And added a nicer slashed zero , a solid cursor and a bar cursor.
\ Only characters with ASCII codes 30 through 126 have definitions provided.

